      "side": 1,
      "message": "We may want Step to be in control of stderr and stdout. Otherwise there\u0027s no real way to separate the stdout/stderr of \"important\" steps from \"infra\" steps around it.\n\nAlso Step could take care of streaming the output off-bot, behind the scenes. Using the exec package directly would make that pretty difficult.\n\nThis probably isn\u0027t something we need to figure out for the initial checkin, but probably should figure it out before rewriting all of our recipes in this framework.\n\n(OTOH, maybe streaming output to the cloud actually *should* be part of the go.skia.org/infra/go/exec package so we could use that feature everywhere. Just a thought.)",
      "range": {
