        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-01T18:43:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed.  It\u0027s also worth reviewing our convention of using sklog.Fatal() in the case of errors inside main(); I want us to be able to write code like we normally would, but it\u0027d probably be easier to control things if we didn\u0027t have to deal with panicking from main().",
