    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "bdb4b6a9_412daad0",
        "filename": "infra/bots/build_task_drivers.sh",
        "patchSetId": 31
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-28T23:01:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Presumably we will want platform in this path and compile for all supported platforms. (At least we would need that for the Skia repo and it might be nice to be consistent in the Infra repo.)",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "dea751d79cd1bdd5607b81eb9fd9a0ec6b19288e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "46175c5e_a2dc4f8b",
        "filename": "infra/bots/build_task_drivers.sh",
        "patchSetId": 31
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-01T18:43:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yep. I haven\u0027t figured out the best way to do that yet.  We won\u0027t want to ship all binaries for every platform to every task.  Ideally, we\u0027d generate a bunch of isolates, where each one is a single task driver (recipe) built for a single platform, but Swarming doesn\u0027t allow us to produce multiple output isolates, so I don\u0027t know how to do this other than having NxM build_task_drivers tasks.",
      "parentUuid": "bdb4b6a9_412daad0",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "dea751d79cd1bdd5607b81eb9fd9a0ec6b19288e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b9154e00_9264abd9",
        "filename": "infra/bots/build_task_drivers.sh",
        "patchSetId": 31
      },
      "lineNbr": 16,
      "author": {
        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-25T19:44:22Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I suspect it will be easiest to have a single compile task and put all the binaries into one isolate. I don\u0027t think the savings in isolated input size will be worth the effort of having different tasks for each platform and binary.\n\nPresumably the compiled binaries will be the same across revisions if the code hasn\u0027t changed, so we wouldn\u0027t have to re-download the isolates for every task. If that isn\u0027t true, we should figure out why.",
      "parentUuid": "46175c5e_a2dc4f8b",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 16,
        "startChar": 14,
        "endLine": 16,
        "endChar": 28
      },
      "revId": "dea751d79cd1bdd5607b81eb9fd9a0ec6b19288e",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
