    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e30160c9_67d05617",
        "filename": "infra/bots/task_drivers/infra_tests.go",
        "patchSetId": 31
      },
      "lineNbr": 0,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-01T18:43:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ideally, all of the built-in components will be extensively tested.  I\u0027m hoping that the task drivers themselves are short and simple enough not to warrant testing.  Doing so would require either full simulation (IMO this is a non-goal) or a way to sandbox the task driver to run it (this would be nice, but is a ton of work and isn\u0027t going to make it into v0).",
