        "id": 5120
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-09-28T23:01:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "It seems like this is all boilerplate that needs to be in every task driver. Maybe that\u0027s not really a problem if we\u0027re just going to copy/paste every time we add a new recipe. However, it would be nice to separate out the non-boilerplate from the boilerplate, e.g. move the \"meat\" of the code into a subroutine, make \"infra_tests\" a constant, add any non-boilerplate flags (none in this example) to a different var section, etc. Maybe even put \"// \u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\u003d\" before/after the interesting parts so it\u0027s easy to zero in.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 17,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 51,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "dea751d79cd1bdd5607b81eb9fd9a0ec6b19288e",
