      "writtenOn": "2018-09-28T23:01:18Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As mentioned in private convo, it would be nice to make CIPD packages, named caches, isolated inputs, and other inputs (e.g. lists of tests) more structured so that a task driver can tell me what it expects to be provided.\n\nE.g. I run \u0027infra_tests --metadata\u0027 and it spits out something like:\n{\n  \"flags\": {\n    \"task_name\": {\n      \"placeholder\": \"TASK_NAME\"\n    },\n    \"repo\": {\n      \"placeholder\": \"REPO\"\n    },\n    ...\n    \"workdir\": {\n      \"named_cache\": \"work\"\n    },\n    \"go\": {\n      \"asset\": \"go\",\n    },\n    ...\n  },\n  \"env\": {\n    \"path\": [\n      {\n        \"asset\": \"node\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"cipd_package\": \"infra/gsutil\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"isolated_input\": \"Housekeeper-PerCommit-BuildTaskDrivers\"\n      }\n    ]\n  }\n}\n\n(Just brainstorming; some of these are probably overkill and it\u0027s not completely clear how others would work. If we\u0027re being super crazy we could pass in the task name, e.g. \u0027skia_perf --metadata --task_name Perf-Win10-Clang-Golo-GPU-GT610-x86_64-Debug-All\u0027 would tell me it depends on Build-Win-Clang-x86_64-Debug, while \u0027skia_perf --metadata --task_name Perf-iOS-Clang-iPadPro-GPU-PowerVRGT7800-arm64-Debug-All\u0027 would say Build-Mac-Clang-arm64-Debug-iOS.)",
      "range": {
